lv.emes.libraries.tools.lists

Class MS_StringList

  • java.lang.Object
    • lv.emes.libraries.tools.lists.MS_StringList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IListActions<java.lang.String>, IPerambulateListActions<java.lang.String>

    public final class MS_StringList
extends java.lang.Object
implements IListActions<java.lang.String>
    Purpose of this class is to store many different but related texts in a list. It implements number of methods for different actions with elements of the list, including perambulation using methods from IListActions. Delimiter works to separate elements each from another when convert this list from big string. secondDelimiter helps in cases when a symbol equal to delimiter is already used in big string.
    Note: those delimiters shouldn't be changed unless they are often used in text which operated with this list.
    Note: class is in it's final implementation state. If there is need for overriding this, use MS_List instead!
    Version:
    2.0.
    See Also:
    MS_List

      • secondDelimiter

        public char secondDelimiter
        Will be used when loading from string which contains some characters with value delimiter that are not actually perform delimiter functions. In this case after delimiter symbol this secondDelimiter symbol will be inserted. Default value for this property is cSecondDefaultDelim.

        delimiter, cSecondDefaultDelim
